article.description: Williams leads Troy to 72-50 win over Texas State
article.headline: Williams leads Troy to 72-50 win over Texas State
article.linkText: Williams leads Troy to 72-50 win over Texas State
article.story: TROY, Ala. -- Hunter Williams scored 19 points, hitting 5 of 9 3-point attempts, to lead Troy to a convincing 72-50 victory over Texas State Saturday night. The victory gives Troy the eighth and final slot in the Sun Belt Conference tournament that begins Thursday in New Orleans. Antonie Myers score 15 points, Kevin Thomas added 13 and Jeff Mullahey had 12 for Troy (11-19, 6-12). Troy held a 33-26 halftime advantage and stretched that 52-35 at the midway point of the second half. The Bobcats could not answer. The Trojans won the rebound battle, pulling down 40 compared to 26 for Texas State. Corey Stern and Kavin Gilder-Tilbury had 10 points apiece for the Bobcats (8-23, 4-14).
